The paper deals with algorithms for finding and counting subgraphs, which are fundamental problems in graph theory and computer science. The techniques used in the paper involve homomorphism polynomials, treewidth, and pathwidth, which are all topics in discrete mathematics and theoretical computer science. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), cs.CG (Computational Geometry), cs.CC (Computational Complexity), and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory).
